cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a network alignment algorithm that uses deep adversarial learning and network embedding. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). However, given the focus on deep learning and the use of adversarial training, cs.LG is the most likely category. The paper also deals with network analysis and alignment, which could place it in cs.SI or cs.DS. The use of embeddings and nearest neighbor alignment could suggest cs.AI or cs.CV as well.
